Laboratory: ALBERTA RESEARCH COUNCIL, INORGANIC ANALYSIS LABORATORY
Analysis method name: Dissolved elements by inductively coupled argon plasma emission spectrometry (ICP-MS).
Sampling comment: WATER LEVELS ARE HIGH! WATER EDGE ~8FT FROM METAL MUSKEG SIGN.  DIRECT FILLED ICPMS, UTLRA-TRACE HG, OIL & GREASE, PAH, NAPTHANICS, F123W EACH SET AT SAME TIME.  COMPED THE REST AND POURED OFF IN 1/3'S EXCEPT NUTRIENTS TOOK 2 SETS OF WINKLERS BOTH AT BOAT LAUNCH. FORWARD OIL AND GREASE SAMPLE TO MAXXAM IN EDMONTON.
